# Component and Icon Usage Guidelines

## UI Components
- Always use components from the `components/ui` folder when possible
- Examples:
  - Use `<Button>` from [src/components/ui/button.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx) instead of HTML `<button>`
  - Use `<Input>` from [src/components/ui/input.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/input.tsx) instead of HTML `<input>`
  - Use `<IconButton>` from [src/components/ui/icon-button.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/icon-button.tsx) for buttons with icons

## Icon Usage
- Always import and use icons from the [src/icons](mdc:src/icons) folder
- Never use third-party icon libraries if equivalent icons exist in the project
- Example: `import { SettingsAltIcon } from '@/icons'`
- Icons should usually use the `--text-secondary` color variable from [src/styles/colors.css](mdc:src/styles/colors.css)
  ```tsx
  // Correct usage
  <SomeIcon className="text-[var(--text-secondary)]" />
  
  // Alternatively, when needing to specify more styles
  <SomeIcon className="text-[var(--text-secondary)] mr-1.5" />
  ```
- All icons should use a standard size of 16 by default:
  ```tsx
  // Correct usage
  <SomeIcon size={16} />
  
  // Incorrect usage
  <SomeIcon size={14} />
  ```
- Only deviate from the standard size when explicitly requested in requirements or when a specific design constraint requires a different size
- This applies to all icon imports from `@/icons` as well as icons from external libraries like `lucide-react`

### Icon Naming Conventions
- Standard icons often include "Default" in their name (e.g., `PageDefaultIcon`, `CheckDefaultIcon`)
- Chevrons and arrows include direction and size information (e.g., `ChevronSmallDownIcon`, `ArrowUpRightIcon`)
- Use regex search to find the right icons when uncertain about naming
- Special size rules:
  - Icons with "24" in the name should be used at size 24 by default (e.g., `ToolbarHelp24Icon`)
  - Icons with "Capability" in the name should be used at size 24 by default
  - Icons with "64" in the name should be used at size 64 by default (e.g., `AddPanelButton64Icon`)

## Component Styling
- Use the component's built-in variant props for styling (e.g., `variant="ghost"`, `size="comfortable"`)
- Minimize custom className additions unless absolutely necessary
- Follow existing style patterns established in the codebase

## Layout Patterns
- Maintain consistent spacing and responsiveness
- Follow existing layout patterns from components like [src/components/Canvas.tsx](mdc:src/components/Canvas.tsx)

## State Management
- Use React hooks for component-level state
- Follow existing patterns for global state from [src/context](mdc:src/context)
